## Known Issues & Lessons Learned

### Docker Networking
- All services use **host IP:port** (192.168.1.143:PORT), never container hostnames
- nginx uses a custom bridge network (172.25.0.0/16) with fixed gateway 172.25.0.1
- nginx proxies to services via `proxy_pass http://172.25.0.1:PORT`
- Container-to-container DNS is fragile — avoid it

### Plex GPU Transcoding
- Requires `LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/nvidia/current:/usr/lib/plexmediaserver/lib`
- Without this, Plex silently falls back to CPU transcoding
- Verify with: `docker exec plex bash -c "CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=0 /usr/lib/plexmediaserver/Plex\ Transcoder -hide_banner -v error -init_hw_device cuda=cu:0 -f lavfi -i nullsrc=s=1920x1080 -t 1 -c:v h264_nvenc -f null /dev/null"`

### Docker Logging
- All containers use journald driver with container name tagging
- Pipeline: Docker → journald → Promtail → Loki
- No json-file log driver — don't add `max-size` or `max-file` options

### Container Permissions
- Redis: runs as UID 999:999 — data dirs must match
- PostgreSQL: runs as UID 999:999 — data dirs need mode 0700
- Most homelab services: UID 1001:1001 (media user)
- Always check container's expected user before creating volume dirs

### Ansible Vault
- Nested structure, not flat: `{{ '{{' }} media_services.plex.api_key {{ '}}' }}` not `{{ '{{' }} vault_plex_api_key {{ '}}' }}`
- Always use `| default('value')` for optional secrets
- Vault password from environment (`ANSIBLE_VAULT_PASSWORD_FILE`), never `--ask-vault-pass`
- Structure reference: `vault/secrets.yaml.template`

### Cloudflare Access
- Use PUT (not PATCH) when assigning reusable policies to applications
- PATCH adds policies on top of auto-created legacy ones
- PUT replaces all policies cleanly

### ComfyUI
- Uses yanwk/comfyui-boot:cu126-slim image (not ai-dock)
- Runs as root (image default)
- Single volume mount: /data01/services/comfyui:/root
- CLI_ARGS: "--fast --use-pytorch-cross-attention"

