## Common Runbooks

### Service Won't Start
1. `systemctl status <service>` — check systemd state
2. `journalctl -u <service> --since "10 min ago"` — check logs
3. `docker compose -f /data01/services/<service>/docker-compose.yml config` — validate compose
4. `docker compose -f /data01/services/<service>/docker-compose.yml up` — try foreground start
5. Check port conflicts: `ss -tlnp | grep <port>`
6. Check disk space: `df -h /data01`

### Container Crash Loop
1. `docker logs <container> --tail 50` — recent logs
2. `docker inspect <container> | jq '.[0].State'` — exit code and OOM status
3. If OOMKilled: increase memory limit in docker-compose template
4. If config error: check template rendering in `/data01/services/<service>/`
5. If image issue: try pulling fresh: `docker compose pull`

### Disk Space Low
1. `docker system prune -f` — remove unused images/containers/networks
2. `journalctl --vacuum-size=1G` — trim journal
3. Check `/data01/services/*/` for oversized logs or data
4. Check Plex transcoder temp: `/data01/services/plex/config/Library/Application Support/Plex Media Server/Cache/Transcode/`

### GPU Issues
1. `nvidia-smi` — check GPU state and utilization
2. `nvidia-smi -r` — reset GPU if hung
3. Check if multiple services competing: llama.cpp + Plex + ComfyUI can't all use GPU simultaneously
4. `DCGM_FI_DEV_GPU_TEMP` in Prometheus — temperature trend

### DNS/Tunnel Issues
1. Check cloudflared: `systemctl status cloudflared` on ocean
2. Check BIND: `dig @192.168.1.2 ocean.home` from any host
3. Check Pi-hole: `dig @192.168.1.9 google.com`
4. Cloudflare dashboard: https://dash.cloudflare.com/ for tunnel status

### Ansible Deployment Failed
1. Read the error message — usually a template rendering issue or missing var
2. `ansible-playbook --syntax-check` — catch YAML errors
3. `ansible-playbook --check` — dry run to catch logic errors
4. Check `vault/secrets.yaml.template` if "dict object has no attribute" errors
5. Common fix: add missing variable to vault with `| default()` fallback

